I dont see any reason not to implement some new illusions.  Why they have not, i have no idea.  I don't know about you but i use werewolf form alot combined with Aug to increase agility.  Saves your butt when you have some serious agro action going on.  So why not continue?  I mean everyone other class that has class based spells continue on all the way to 60. <BR>Mages get damage shields and awesome AOE's.<BR>Wizards get nasty DD and translocate spells.<BR>Shamans get have lots of stat increasing buffs and later on group buffs.<BR>Druids get all sorts of DD and buffing spells<BR>Clerics.. sheesh i dont even need to go their<BR>we all know what kinda HP & AC buffs they have<P>which leaves us enchanters.<BR>what do we do?<BR>1. crowd control<BR>2.increase mana<BR>3. weak player buffs.<BR>4. Illusions<P>1. yes we do crown control. which up until lvl 54 the spell line up is great. Afterwards<BR>we dont get any. we get a few low resist mez spells that have a very short duration.<P>2. Increase mana. 16 breeze, 30 clarity.<BR>52. group clarity.(which is only good for two lvls, after you get to 54 youll never use it again). 54 the famed clarity 2 and at 58 group clarity. The gift of magic and increase int and wis buffs are close to usless. I mean come on by the time you get the spells your INT and WIS are prolly 200 already. Gift of Magic adds to your max mana.<BR>well.... if your in a good group you will never reach full mana to begin with so whats the point?<P>3.player buffs. what do we have? minor AC buffs and speed buffs. The ac buffs are close to nothing. lvl 49 you get shadow 20 ac. lvl 56 you get Umbra ac 23 !! 3 AC for going from lvl 49 to 56 !!! sheesh. the speed buffs i think are well spaced out as far as where in life you get them. and GRM is really the only group buff we get otehr then broup clarity. what about a group beserk spell?? If we are the kings of mana why can we not transfer mana like a Necro? sure we can drain mana. but why not transfer mana? necros shouldnt be able to do it in the first place. transfer health. yes. mana.. no<BR>being a health stealing class has nothing to do with mana.<P>4. Illusions. WHY NOT ??? make are class to powerful??? BAH its not like we can cast them on other. they are self only. i think that we should have more spells like Boon of garou. difrent varites for diffrent scenarios.Boon for tanks. maybe somthing for casters. Boon procs life tap. why not have one for casters that procs a small mana transfer spell? get those casters into battle. its not practical but HEY.. you know it would be fun seeing your buddy wizard turning into a mana sucking monster   <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0">)<P>Well im sorry for venting. Do me a favor and take a look at the spell line ups for all casting classes and take a look at enchanters after lvl 54. nothing till lvl 60<BR>And illusions no more after lvl 44 why not?? i just want a few reasons why.<BR>they dont all have to be some serious tweak. but fun. Thats what counts.
