<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Well, OK, our AC buffs are pretty stinky (by testimonial, they are always the first to be overwritten), but that's not really the forte of Enchanters... I'd narrow your above list to the primary 2: Speed and Crowd Control.<P>Speed: Chanters have the best independant Mana buffs in the game (AKA no need to be grouped).   Not to mention they stack nicely with others.  No one will ever turn down Clarity.  The melee speed buffs are among the best in the game as well.   No one speeds up group member's offensive abilities better than Chanters.  And by extention, we have great speed debuffs, again both mana wise (at higher lvls) and attack rate. <P>Crowd Control:  Well, duh.  Undisputed kings, and to the point where Chanters are required for some places.   I completely understand why VI had to scale back our Mezzing capabilities in higher lvl dungeons... a good group could devastate a high lvl dungeon if your chanter could keep half of the mobs mezzed.   Besides, boosting MR in high lvl mobs was nessisary for game dynamics, otherwise a Chanter and a Wizzard could AE Mez / Root / Nuke their way thru any dungeon without any need of a tank or healer. <P>Illusions are not, in combat situations anyway, terribly useful.  I would still say they are a class defining ability, but not one that needs "Balancing" per say.  There is a concern that enchanters could walk thru dungeons without fear of attack (ie if we had a Gnoll illusion, and could walk freely thru Paw), and we all know how much VI hates the idea that we might not appreciate every single foot of ground you battle thru... heh heh.  And I do understand that rational.  So no, illusions aren't NEEDED, really, except for maybe two little exemptions: class consistancy and customer satisfaction.   As pointed out above, just about every class defining ability starts at around lvl 1 and goes thru level 60, except for Illusions, which do start at lvl 1, and consistantly build until lvl 44, when they abruptly stop.   It almost seems as if VI simply ran out of ideas.   And of course, as I said above, this is an old and worn arguement (dang, I find myself drug back into it again... doh), which is evidence enough that VI's enchanter playing group is dissatisfied with the apparent lack of concern / attention.<P>OK, OK, we all know that Illusions, outside racial, are really just for fun, with some minor ability that might occasionally be useful.  I can see where VI would allocate their energy towards more "important" matters, because lets all face the fact... basically illusions are really only for fun.  <P>Oh, wait, isn't that what the whole game is for?  I forget sometimes.   Ya, that would be my point. <P><Sigh>  Didn't mean to get back into this.  I do think we'll see a couple more, someday, when the dev. team runs out of other things to do (<snicker>), or there is an Enchanter Strike (which would be evil... heh heh).  I expect they'll for the time being have their hands full with re-configuring all our old illusions into the new game engine.  Maybe soon after that they may patch some in.  <P>But i'm not holding  my breath, still.  :P<P>Cylos the Cynic
</FONT>
