<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Grubber: <I>1. yes we do crown control. which up until lvl 54 the spell line up is great. Afterwards we dont get any. we get a few low resist mez spells that have a very short duration.</I><P>I'd love to have better upgrades to this line. I find that any time I have to control a 55+ mob I run out of mana really really quickly. GoK might need to have it's mana requirements scaled back just slightly. There are options but not a whole lot.<P><I>2. Increase mana. 16 breeze, 30 clarity. 52. group clarity.(which is only good for two lvls, after you get to 54 youll never use it again). 54 the famed clarity 2 and at 58 group clarity. The gift of magic and increase int and wis buffs are close to usless. I mean come on by the time you get the spells your INT and WIS are prolly 200 already. Gift of Magic adds to your max mana. well.... if your in a good group you will never reach full mana to begin with so whats the point?<P>3.player buffs. what do we have? minor AC buffs and speed buffs. The ac buffs are close to nothing. lvl 49 you get shadow 20 ac. lvl 56 you get Umbra ac 23 !! 3 AC for going from lvl 49 to 56 !!! sheesh. the speed buffs i think are well spaced out as far as where in life you get them. and GRM is really the only group buff we get otehr then broup clarity. what about a group beserk spell?? If we are the kings of mana why can we not transfer mana like a Necro? sure we can drain mana. but why not transfer mana? necros shouldnt be able to do it in the first place. transfer health. yes. mana.. no being a health stealing class has nothing to do with mana.</I><P>The clarity line is arguable one of the most power spell lines in the game. No if's and's or's or but's. The only reason there is group downtime is due to mana restraints and if a group had unlimited mana they'd burn through a whole zone. These spells quicken the mana regeneration rate thereby lessening downtime. Haste. Another awesome spell line. Haste allows you to mow down mobs so much quicker. Slows. Not as good as a shaman's slows but still very highly rated. And at level 57 it is nearly as good as a shaman's haste to not matter at 70% slow rate coupled with an enchanter's haste which at 54 does 64% haste. Augment at level 56 is also a great spell as it does decent haste as well as adds ac to the melee who has a good haste item equipped. It's also great to cast on your healers as this adds to their ac. I would argue that the mist line of AC spells we get are far from useless. Yes it's weaker than the cleric ones but it's better than none at all and it stacks with augment/ation. So with the augment line and the mist line of spells, I can self buff roughly 30-50ac depending on level. That's not a small gain. I've been in groups without clerics in Sebilis and this spell is great to cast on your tanks and secondary healers. I heard that Gift of Insight and Gift of Brilliance also adds to mana regeneration rate and it doesn't stack with the Druid's Protection of the Glades so they might have something there. I have not tested this so I'm unsure if it's true or not. I do wish we get the mana transfer spells as well. Too often I have mana while the cleric doesn't although the reverse has also been true.<P><I>4. Illusions. WHY NOT ??? make are class to powerful??? BAH its not like we can cast them on other. they are self only. i think that we should have more spells like Boon of garou. difrent varites for diffrent scenarios.Boon for tanks. maybe somthing for casters. Boon procs life tap. why not have one for casters that procs a small mana transfer spell? get those casters into battle. its not practical but HEY.. you know it would be fun seeing your buddy wizard turning into a mana sucking monster)</I><P>Illusions at this point are mostly for fun (though there are plenty of situational use on some of them). Arguably the most useful overall is the fire elemental spell for it's damage shield. A boon of garou styled spell that procs mana tap for casters is useless. Due to the nature of procs as well as a caster's low meleeing skills it's far far more efficient to just park your backside down and med up.
</FONT>
